# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: MarionOrVargaPath
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "It was more than two weeks after the victory over the eastern tribesmen, when Sarah arrived early for a council meeting, surprised to find the room already full."
    new "It was more than two weeks after the victory over the eastern tribesmen, when Sarah arrived early for a council meeting, surprised to find the room already full."

    old "There was a busy chatter, which suddenly felt silent as everyone noticed Sarah."
    new "There was a busy chatter, which suddenly felt silent as everyone noticed Sarah."

    old "Thomas was sitting back in this throne, waiving at Sarah excitedly as she approached."
    new "Thomas was sitting back in this throne, waiving at Sarah excitedly as she approached."

    old "Sarah had almost reached the table, when suddenly, Marion stood up."
    new "Sarah had almost reached the table, when suddenly, Marion stood up."

    old "Sarah saw Thomas suppress laughter. In between his laughs he managed to speak."
    new "Sarah saw Thomas suppress laughter. In between his laughs he managed to speak."

    old "I believe our honorable friend, Marion, has something he wanted to say to you."
    new "I believe our honorable friend, Marion, has something he wanted to say to you."

    old "Sarah could feel a pit in her stomach."
    new "Sarah could feel a pit in her stomach."

    old "She feared she already knew what he was planning to do."
    new "She feared she already knew what he was planning to do."

    old "Confused, Sarah stared at Marion."
    new "Confused, Sarah stared at Marion."

    old "Marion fell to one knee, and extended a hand, holding a small box carved out of oak."
    new "Marion fell to one knee, and extended a hand, holding a small box carved out of oak."

    old "Sarah Rose, having given it serious consideration, I wish to pronounce in front of all these people, my love for you."
    new "Sarah Rose, having given it serious consideration, I wish to pronounce in front of all these people, my love for you."

    old "Please give me the honour of your hand, and I will swear to always be true."
    new "Please give me the honour of your hand, and I will swear to always be true."

    old "Stunned, Sarah felt it almost physically difficult to remain standing."
    new "Stunned, Sarah felt it almost physically difficult to remain standing."

    old "The edges of her vision seemed to blur, and the ground under her feet began to shift."
    new "The edges of her vision seemed to blur, and the ground under her feet began to shift."

    old "Yes."
    new "Yes."

    old "The words seemed to slip out before she had given it any thought."
    new "The words seemed to slip out before she had given it any thought."

    old "She saw the faces around the table, clearly, she was not alone in her surprised."
    new "She saw the faces around the table, clearly, she was not alone in her surprised."

    old "Still on his knees, she saw Marion's face beaming."
    new "Still on his knees, she saw Marion's face beaming."

    old "She watched as he rose to his feet, grabbed her by the waist and spun her around."
    new "She watched as he rose to his feet, grabbed her by the waist and spun her around."

    old "All around the room, people began to give their congratulations to the new couple."
    new "All around the room, people began to give their congratulations to the new couple."

    old "Varga was the only one who carried a pained expression on his face."
    new "Varga was the only one who carried a pained expression on his face."

    old "Sarah watched it all unfold as if this was happening to someone else."
    new "Sarah watched it all unfold as if this was happening to someone else."

    old "Reject Marion's proposal."
    new "Reject Marion's proposal."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah felt all the emotions of the shock pushed out and she found her footing again."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah felt all the emotions of the shock pushed out and she found her footing again."

    old "Rage was now keeping her tethered."
    new "Rage was now keeping her tethered."

    old "In only two broad steps she closed the distance between herself and Marion, standing over the imbecile as he was still kneeling."
    new "In only two broad steps she closed the distance between herself and Marion, standing over the imbecile as he was still kneeling."

    old "A more humble man would have seen the signs of what came next, but Marion was not humble."
    new "A more humble man would have seen the signs of what came next, but Marion was not humble."

    old "A shattering crack rang out across the room, followed by a deafening silence."
    new "A shattering crack rang out across the room, followed by a deafening silence."

    old "Marion's face was frozen off to the side, unable to process the slap, either physically or emotionally."
    new "Marion's face was frozen off to the side, unable to process the slap, either physically or emotionally."

    old "Sarah could see from the corners of her eyes that everyone was staring at her."
    new "Sarah could see from the corners of her eyes that everyone was staring at her."

    old "Marriage?"
    new "Marriage?"

    old "Are you insane?"
    new "Are you insane?"

    old "We were nothing more than friends at best, Marion."
    new "We were nothing more than friends at best, Marion."

    old "I never gave you my blessing, I never agreed to any of this."
    new "I never gave you my blessing, I never agreed to any of this."

    old "And if you thought I would feel forced to say yes because we were in public, you're as big of an idiot as you are craven."
    new "And if you thought I would feel forced to say yes because we were in public, you're as big of an idiot as you are craven."

    old "The only thing you've managed to do today is humiliate me, and make a joke of yourself."
    new "The only thing you've managed to do today is humiliate me, and make a joke of yourself."

    old "Marion was now crawling away from her, trying to recover and get back on his feet."
    new "Marion was now crawling away from her, trying to recover and get back on his feet."

    old "By the time he had gotten onto his feet, Sarah could see his face had turned bright red."
    new "By the time he had gotten onto his feet, Sarah could see his face had turned bright red."

    old "I brought it up with Thomas...he thought it would be..."
    new "I brought it up with Thomas...he thought it would be..."

    old "A joke, Marion. He probably thought you were a joke, and I suppose, in that regard, he was right."
    new "A joke, Marion. He probably thought you were a joke, and I suppose, in that regard, he was right."

    old "I don't want to see you here ever again. You're off the council."
    new "I don't want to see you here ever again. You're off the council."

    old "Leave, and pray that nobody ever hears how much you humiliated yourself today."
    new "Leave, and pray that nobody ever hears how much you humiliated yourself today."

    old "Marion searched for words, but unable to find any, turned around and stormed off."
    new "Marion searched for words, but unable to find any, turned around and stormed off."

    old "Sarah snapped back to the table full of advisors."
    new "Sarah snapped back to the table full of advisors."

    old "Her eyes ran across all the faces. Most were a mix of stunned and mortified, there was only one exception."
    new "Her eyes ran across all the faces. Most were a mix of stunned and mortified, there was only one exception."

    old "Varga was brightly smiling, clearly having enjoyed the humiliation of Marion."
    new "Varga was brightly smiling, clearly having enjoyed the humiliation of Marion."

    old "If I find out any of you set him up to this, I swear you're going to pay for it."
    new "If I find out any of you set him up to this, I swear you're going to pay for it."

    old "Sarah herself now turned around and stormed off, in no mood to continue the council meeting."
    new "Sarah herself now turned around and stormed off, in no mood to continue the council meeting."

